==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[gebed|ġebed]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /bi:d/

===Noun===
'''bead''' ''plural'' '''beads'''
# ''(Archaic)'' [[prayer]]
# each of a string of small balls making up the [[rosary]] or [[paternoster]]
# a small round object with a hole to allow it to be threaded on a cord or wire.
# a small [[drop]] of water or other liquid.
#:''beads of sweat''

